  <h1>Getting Started</h1>
  <p>After installation, open the Web UI at <code>http://localhost:5000</code> (or your server’s IP and port).</p>

  <h2>Create your first monitor</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Click <strong>Add Monitor</strong>.</li>
    <li>Enter a name, the URL to watch, check interval (e.g. 300 seconds), match type (string or regex), pattern to look for, and notification email.</li>
    <li>Click save. The monitor will run on schedule; use the play button on the card to run a check immediately.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Verify notifications</h2>
  <p>Use <strong>Test Email</strong> in the header to confirm SMTP is configured. Add Discord or Slack in Advanced Options if you use them.</p>

